      • aTan0

        public static double aTan0(double y,
                           double x)
        The full-circle arc-tangent of a slope represented as x and y coordinates returned as floating-point degrees. The sine of aTan0(y,x) = y, and the cosine of aTan0(y,x) = x.

        TrakSim uses a (TV) raster coordinate system where (0,0) is the northwest or upper left corner, and angles are in degrees clockwise from north.

        Parameters:
        y - The floating-point sine component of the angle
        x - The floating-point cosine component of the angle
        Returns:
        The angle in degrees, between -180 and +180

      • Angle2cart

        public static void Angle2cart(double degs)
        The inverse function of aTan0, which returns both sine and cosine.

        TrakSim uses a (TV) raster coordinate system where (0,0) is the northwest or upper left corner, and angles are in degrees clockwise from north.

        Parameters:
        degs - The floating-point angle in degrees
